🏁 Race Bot (ESP32 + BTS7960B)

🚀 Overview

This project is a high-performance Bluetooth-controlled race bot built using an ESP32 and dual BTS7960B motor drivers. It is designed for off-road racing competitions where precise control, smooth acceleration, and responsive turning are critical.

The control system has been optimized to achieve:

Smooth acceleration and deceleration

Precise curve control during motion

Instant response to joystick release (no drift)

Stable high-speed performance



---

⚙️ Hardware Used

ESP32 DevKit V1

2x BTS7960B Motor Drivers

4x 300 RPM 12V Metal Geared Motors

4x Li-ion Batteries (3.7V each, in series)

Custom chassis



---

🎮 Control System (Key Features)

1. Differential Drive Logic

The bot uses differential steering:

Left motor speed = throttle + steering

Right motor speed = throttle - steering



---

2. Smooth Acceleration & Braking

Two smoothing constants are used:

accelRate = 0.2 → smooth acceleration

decelRate = 0.5 → faster braking response


This prevents jerks and improves stability on rough terrain.


---

3. Precision Curve Control

Steering is NOT smoothed

Uses cubic exponential mapping for fine control


Result:

Small joystick input → gentle curve

Large input → aggressive turn



---

4. Instant Straight Correction

When steering joystick is released:

Steering is immediately forced to zero

Bot continues straight without drift



---

5. Hard Stop Logic

When all joystick inputs are zero:

Motor speeds are instantly set to zero

Eliminates unwanted rolling



---

6. Dynamic Steering Gain

Steering sensitivity reduces at high speed:

steeringGain = 0.8 - (speedFactor * 0.4)

This prevents instability at high velocity.


---

7. Turn Speed Reduction

During curves:

Peak speed is reduced dynamically (~45%)


This improves grip and prevents slipping.


---

8. Exponential PWM Mapping

Custom expoMap() function ensures:

Smooth low-speed control

Strong high-speed output



---

🧠 Control Philosophy

Throttle → smooth and stable

Steering → instant and precise

No residual motion

No input lag


This mimics professional RC racing control behavior.


---

🛠️ Code Structure

parseCommand() → reads Bluetooth input

driveMotors() → main control logic

expoMap() → PWM shaping



---

📡 Bluetooth Control Format

Commands are received as:

FxxxBxxxLxxxRxxx

Where:

F = Forward

B = Backward

L = Left

R = Right


Each value ranges from 000 to 255.


---

🏎️ Performance Characteristics

Fast acceleration without jerks

Stable high-speed straight runs

Precise cornering control

Immediate response to user input



---

⚠️ Notes

Heatsinks on BTS7960B drivers are recommended for high load usage

Ensure proper wiring and power distribution

Off-road conditions may introduce vibrations; secure all components properly



---

